  <dcvalue element="description" qualifier="abstract">The principle of probation, as applied to offenders against the state--whether such offenders be adults or minors--was originally applied in a limited, way to proceedings in criminal courts. As with all reforms, it came first in a rather limited fashion-generally as to misdemeanors and first offenders; gradually it was extended to more serious offenses.</dcvalue>
